boxplot(kehtna_fluxes$N2O~kehtna_fluxes$plot)

# FULL PERIOD

t.test(N2O ~ plot, data = kehtna_fluxes)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  N2O by plot
## t = 2.2538, df = 407.81, p-value = 0.02474
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##   30.62524 448.63518
## sample estimates:
## mean in group 1 mean in group 2 
##        748.0512        508.4210
# PERIOD: 05/08 - 25/08

t.test(N2O ~ plot, data = kehtna_fluxes[kehtna_fluxes$date2<"2016-09-25",])
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  N2O by plot
## t = 2.8073, df = 137.21, p-value = 0.005724
